<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-579-997  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 579 997.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Magazine  Nov 1990 v5 n11 p177(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Telecon Library Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New Attachmate Now! (Attachmate's Now! PC/Host Autoware 1.1automated scripting language) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Attachmate Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   NOW! PC/Host Autoware 1.1 (Communications software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Program Development ToolsUtility ProgramsProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>New Attachmate Now!andM;The latest version of Now!andP;  PC/Host Autoware 1.1 is shipping from Attachmate.andO;Now! is an automated scripting language that can be used to make almost anyrepetitive LAN-to-mainframe task simpler.andM;Instead of learning the arcane syntax of mainframe commands, LAN users cansimply pick an action off a menu.andP;  Behind the scenes, a program written withNow! jumps into action, executing the mundane task, such as logging into themainframe, retrieving PROFS messages, or collecting information from adatabase.andP;  Now! allows LAN users to concentrate on their jobs and not puzzleover how to access the mainframe.andM;Version 1.1 sports mouse point-and-click capability, pop-up dialogue boxes,and pull-down menus.andP;  New data manipulation features include arrays, stringhandling macros, and decimal number support.andP;  Two &quot;learn&quot; utilities, whichsimplifies writing programs, are also new.andM;Now! resides on the PC and consists of a series of English-like macros.andO;Using Now! macros and the sample Autoware programs included, an administrator(who isn't necessarily a superb programmer) can write frontend applications.andO;The macros eliminate the need to learn IBM High Level Language ApplicationsProgramming Interface (HLLAPI) or C.andM;Now! uses a 3270 emulator that supports HLLAPI, which works with a variety ofLAN-to-mainframe connections, including gateways and the Token Ring InterfaceCoupler.andM;Two versions are available.andP;  The author's version costs $565; the end-user'sversion costs $195.andP;  Upgrades from version 1.0 are free.andM;Attachmate, 13231 SE 36th St., Bellevue, Wash.andP;  98006, (206) 644-4010.andO;</TEXT></DOC>